==Finnish==

===Adjective===
'''nasta''' (nastempi, nastoin)

# (slang) [[cool]], [[neat]], [[great]]

===Finnish synonyms===
*[[siisti]] (lit. [[clean]])
*[[mainio]], [[oiva]]

===Noun===

'''nasta''' (plural ''nastat'')

# [[pin]]
# [[stud]] (as in studded tyres)
# [[tack]]

===Usage notes===

In automotive technology slang, plural case ''nastat'' almost invariably refers to studded tyres.
* ''Laitoin nastat alle jo lokakuussa, kun ensilumi tuli.'' I swapped the studded tyres on in October already, when the first snow came.

===Derived terms===
*nastahammas - pin-mounted [[tooth]] [[implant]]
*nastarengas - studded [[tyre]]

